-- Seed — entity registry (Phase 5 SP1, recursive interest picker)
--
-- Source of truth: interest_picker.html's DATA const (the approved prototype's full
-- seed dataset). Rows are LIFTED (not re-authored) — every entity_id is the prototype's
-- path-derived chip id: idBase + '/' + slug(label), where slug = lowercase, non-alnum -> '-',
-- trimmed. entity_slug == entity_id. entity_parent_slug is the seeding set-id (the
-- listEntities scope). Only ENTITY nodes (those with a `kind`) are seeded — pure TOPIC
-- nodes live in the `interests` taxonomy (supabase/seed/interests.sql), not here.
--
-- Depends on migration 0007 (entities table + entity_kind enum). Run AFTER migrations.
-- IDEMPOTENT: `on conflict (entity_id) do nothing` — safe to re-run. 248 rows
-- across 6 categories. Labels with apostrophes (A''ja Wilson) are
-- SQL-escaped; tickers with dots (BRK.B, ENR.DE) are plain text.

-- ── AI (14) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
on conflict (entity_id) do nothing;

